Write a Java program that calculates Fibonacci numbers based on user input.

Problem Definition

The Fibonacci sequence is:

0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21, ...


Each number is the sum of the previous two numbers.

Formula:

F(0) = 0, F(1) = 1
F(n) = F(n-1) + F(n-2), for n > 1


Example:

Input: n = 6

Output: 8 (Sequence: 0,1,1,2,3,5,8)




// code example//

import java.util.Scanner;

public class FibonacciUserInput {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Take user input
        System.out.print("Enter the position n: ");
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        // Edge cases
        if (n == 0) {
            System.out.println("Fibonacci number at position 0 is 0");
            return;
        }
        if (n == 1) {
            System.out.println("Fibonacci number at position 1 is 1");
            return;
        }

        // Iterative calculation
        int a = 0, b = 1, c = 0;
        for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
            c = a + b;
            a = b;
            b = c;
        }

        System.out.println("Fibonacci number at position " + n + " is " + c);
    }
}




Enter the position n: 6
Fibonacci number at position 6 is 8

